## Alp region hosts 50 karst springs from 4 countries:
01- Austria (44 karst springs)
02- France (1 karst spring)
03- Slovenia (4 karst springs)
04- Germany (1 karst spring)

Austrian data is provided by 

Simon Seelig (simon.seelig@uni-graz.at), 
Jutta Eybl (Jutta.EYBL@bmluk.gv.at), and 
Gerfried Winkler (gerfried.winkler@uni-graz.at). 

Original data source is "https://ehyd.gv.at". 
Austrian data is licensed by the original data provider CC BY-NC 4.0. 

French data is provided by 

Bruno Arfib (arfib@cerege.fr) and 
Nathan Rispal (rispal@cerege.fr). 

Original data source is the SNO Karst database "https://sokarst.org".

Slovenian data is provided by 

Natasa Ravbar (natasa.ravbar@zrc-sazu.si) and 
Cyril Mayaud (cyril.mayaud@zrc-sazu.si). 

Original data source is "https://vode.arso.gov.si"

German data is downloaded from Bavarian Hydrometeorological Service "https://www.gkd.bayern.de/en/groundwater/flow-of-springs/tables"

For more information, please see Metadata table.
